OL,4,Cwho was stabbed 17 times in his own bed
OL,6,F"Three doctors have independently
OL,7,Flooked at the circumstances of this
OL,8,Fcase, and each independently reached
OL,9,Fconclusions. The conclusions of each
OL,10,Fof them are that Benjamin Moglione
OL,11,Fundoubtedly suffered from epilepsy and
OL,12,Fthat it was not properly controlled,
OL,13,Fthe consequences of which were that he
OL,14,Fsuffered seizures and sometimes
OL,15,Fclusters of seizures.
OL,17,F"That resulted in postictal psychosis.
OL,18,FIt is a common occurrence as a result
OL,19,Fof uncontrolled clusters of seizures
OL,20,Fthat is often associated with a range
OL,21,Fof psychotic symptoms.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/9
