OL,3,CStudent admits killing his stepdad,
OL,4,Cwho was stabbed 17 times in his own bed
OL,6,F"The doctors each concluded that, at
OL,7,Fthe time of the killing, Mr Moglione,
OL,8,Fthey are of the firm conclusion, was
OL,9,Fsuffering from postictal psychosis,
OL,10,Fsecondary to his uncontrolled frontal
OL,11,Flobe epilepsy, and that medical
OL,12,Fconclusion explains why it is that
OL,13,Fthis very tragic event happened.
OL,14,FAnother potential issue is whether or
OL,15,Fnot his medical condition was so
OL,16,Fsevere on that night that his actions
OL,17,Fwere, in effect, unconscious actions
OL,18,Fand whether or not a defence of
OL,19,Fautomatism was available to him.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/9
