OL,3,CStudent admits killing his stepdad,
OL,4,Cwho was stabbed 17 times in his own bed
OL,6,F"The medical evidence in relation to
OL,7,Fthat is now clear. The medical
OL,8,Fevidence now is that, while he was
OL,9,Fsuffering from postictal psychosis,
OL,10,Fthe defendant was aware of what he was
OL,11,Fdoing and was aware that it was wrong.
OL,13,F"He was not unconscious and he was not
OL,14,Fsleepwalking at the time he did it.
OL,15,FThe complete defence of automatism is
OL,16,Fnot available, but there is evidence
OL,17,Fcapable of supporting the partial
OL,18,Fdefence of diminished responsibility."
